The paper deals with the Choquet integral, which is a tool commonly used in artificial intelligence and decision making (cs.AI). It also involves the geometric realization of lattices and their triangulation, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses bisubmodular functions, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The concept of bicooperative games is also mentioned, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). Lastly, the paper includes an application to multicriteria aggregation, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
